[
    {
        "content": "<p>Can <code>recall</code> be used on <code>structure</code> declarations?</p>",
        "id": 514632012,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1745749235
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Have you tried?</p>",
        "id": 514740643,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1745825705
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Of course I tried, but I don't know if it failed because I didn't know the right syntax or because it isn't supported.</p>",
        "id": 514760889,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1745831466
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <code>recall</code> was intended only for recalling theorems/lemmas. Maybe it should be generalized.</p>",
        "id": 514761509,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1745831626
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It works very well for definitions.</p>",
        "id": 514761611,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1745831646
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, but I think that's just an unintended side effect of the current implementation.</p>",
        "id": 514761712,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1745831675
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I use it to provide a summary of the main results of our project in the sink file:<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/Ivan-Sergeyev/seymour/blob/main/Seymour.lean\">https://github.com/Ivan-Sergeyev/seymour/blob/main/Seymour.lean</a></p>",
        "id": 514761813,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1745831703
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sure, I'm not saying your request is unreasonable. Far from it.</p>",
        "id": 514762159,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1745831796
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, I am all for generalizing <code>recall</code> to cover more kinds of declarations.</p>",
        "id": 514762562,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1745831904
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe the syntax should become</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">recall</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">lemma</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">recall</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">def</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">recall</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">inductive</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">recall</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">structure</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 514763080,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1745832022
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And instead of having <code>lemma</code>/<code>def</code>/etc complain about <code> `Foo.Bar` is already declared</code>, it would catch that error, and do the <code>recall</code> check of whether the existing decl matches the current one.</p>",
        "id": 514764111,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1745832291
    }
]